JIRA's full content view now uses CSS to force pagebreaks between issues.  This works in IE6 (see JRA-4226), but apparently causes excessive whitespace around issues.  See Neal's excellent summary at:

http://forums.atlassian.com/thread.jspa?messageID=257218940&#257218940

Since it seems to be something users might normally wish to tweak, we should move this option to the General Configuration page.

This is also an issue I raised on the mailing list.

I am having a problem with the ordering when adding options through the OptionsManager API.

I've seen the several different behaviors: Insertion order (1,2,3,4), opposite insertion order (4,3,2,1), and (when running with HSQLDB) reverse ordered pairs (2,1,4,3 instead of 1,2,3,4).

I am using the following code:

   Options options = optionsManager.getOptions(config);
   List createdOptions = createOptions(); //  returns correctly order list of options
   for (Iterator i = createdOptions.iterator(); i.hasNext();) {
     String value = i.next().toString();
     Option option = options.addOption(null, value);
   }
   optionsManager.updateOptions(options);

I've also tried forcing a reorder after each add using

  options.moveToStartSequence(option);

But this required refreshing the options between calls which in turn proved unacceptably slow, and feels wrong in any case.  Is there some other method I should be using to add options to ensure the order I want?  What is the best way of populating the options in a particular order?

